cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper is about using adversarial machine learning to generate explanations for incorrect classifications made by Intrusion Detection Systems (IDSs). This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on the interpretability of machine learning models in the context of IDSs, which is a common concern in the field of machine learning for security applications.
